<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warm., Danske Vid. Selsk. Skrift. Ser .. VI, 9: 147" authorityYear="1899" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Leiothylax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leiothylax quangensis" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Leiothylax quangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been assessed for the IUCN Red List as Endangered (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B41" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010m. Leiothylaxquangensis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185346A8392899. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Leiothylaxquangensis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185346 A 8392899. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 m">Ghogue 2010m</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon is known from one locality, Edea waterfalls. The area of occupancy and extent of occurrence are both estimated at 2 km2 each. The hydropower dam at Edea will certainly impact the quality of the habitat of the species. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. quangensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="quangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">L. quangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reassessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
